# NexusHub Backend

FastAPI backend for the NexusHub academic research discovery engine.

---

## Quick Start

```bash
# 1. Install dependencies
pip install -r requirements.txt

# 2. Run (databases must be in the same directory, or set env vars)
uvicorn main:app --reload --port 8000

# 3. Open index.html in your browser
```

---

## Environment Variables

| Variable | Default | Description |
|---|---|---|
| `NEXUS_DB` | `nexushub.db` | Path to the main nexushub SQLite database |
| `KNOWLEDGE_DB` | `knowledge.db` | Path to the embeddings database |
| `OPENALEX_EMAIL` | `nexushub@example.com` | Email for OpenAlex polite pool (faster rate limits) |

---

## API Endpoints

| Method | Path | Description |
|---|---|---|
| GET | `/search?q=&limit=50` | Semantic / FTS paper search |
| GET | `/paper/{id}?enrich=true` | Full paper detail with auto-enrichment |
| GET | `/paper/{id}/graph?depth=2&limit=50` | Citation graph |
| GET | `/paper/{id}/bridges?limit=6` | Cross-domain bridge papers |
| GET | `/paper/{id}/enrich?force=false` | Explicit OpenAlex enrichment |
| GET | `/communities` | All research communities |
| GET | `/community/{id}/papers?limit=20` | Papers in a community |
| GET | `/trending?limit=30` | Top papers by PageRank |
| GET | `/fields` | Field overlap matrix |
| GET | `/bridge-concepts?limit=20` | Bridge concepts across fields |
| GET | `/evolution?concept=&top_n=10` | Concept growth over time |
| GET | `/cache/stats` | Enrichment cache statistics |
| GET | `/health` | Health check |

---

## Database Schema (nexushub.db)

The backend expects these tables — create them when building your DB pipeline:

```sql
-- Core
CREATE TABLE papers (
    paper_id        TEXT PRIMARY KEY,
    title           TEXT,
    doi             TEXT,
    year            INTEGER,
    journal         TEXT,
    citation_count  INTEGER,
    abstract        TEXT,
    community       INTEGER
);

CREATE TABLE authors (
    author_id  TEXT PRIMARY KEY,
    name       TEXT
);

CREATE TABLE paper_authors (
    paper_id   TEXT REFERENCES papers,
    author_id  TEXT REFERENCES authors,
    position   INTEGER
);

CREATE TABLE concepts (
    concept_id  TEXT PRIMARY KEY,
    name        TEXT,
    level       INTEGER,    -- 0 = top-level field
    wikidata    TEXT
);

CREATE TABLE paper_concepts (
    paper_id    TEXT REFERENCES papers,
    concept_id  TEXT REFERENCES concepts,
    score       REAL
);

CREATE TABLE citations (
    paper_id        TEXT REFERENCES papers,
    cited_paper_id  TEXT
);

CREATE TABLE paper_scores (
    paper_id        TEXT PRIMARY KEY REFERENCES papers,
    pagerank        REAL,
    hub_score       REAL,
    authority_score REAL
);

CREATE TABLE communities (
    community_id  INTEGER PRIMARY KEY,
    label         TEXT,
    top_concepts  TEXT,   -- JSON array of strings
    paper_count   INTEGER,
    avg_year      REAL
);

CREATE TABLE bridge_concepts (
    concept_id   TEXT PRIMARY KEY,
    name         TEXT,
    fields       TEXT,     -- JSON array of field names
    field_count  INTEGER,
    bridge_score REAL
);

CREATE TABLE field_overlap (
    field_a         TEXT,
    field_b         TEXT,
    shared_concepts INTEGER,
    overlap_score   REAL,
    PRIMARY KEY (field_a, field_b)
);

CREATE TABLE concept_evolution (
    concept_id   TEXT REFERENCES concepts,
    year         INTEGER,
    paper_count  INTEGER,
    avg_citations REAL,
    PRIMARY KEY (concept_id, year)
);

-- Written by the backend automatically:
CREATE TABLE enriched_cache (
    paper_id    TEXT PRIMARY KEY,
    fetched_at  INTEGER,
    success     INTEGER DEFAULT 0,
    oa_data     TEXT    -- JSON blob from OpenAlex
);
```

## knowledge.db Schema

```sql
-- Raw blobs (float32, little-endian)
CREATE TABLE paper_embeddings (
    paper_id   TEXT PRIMARY KEY,
    embedding  BLOB
);

-- sqlite-vec virtual table for KNN search
CREATE VIRTUAL TABLE vec_papers USING vec0(
    paper_id TEXT PRIMARY KEY,
    embedding FLOAT[384]   -- dimension matches your model
);
```

## Vector Search

If `sentence-transformers` is installed, `/search` uses:
- Model: `all-MiniLM-L6-v2` (384-dim)
- KNN via `sqlite-vec` cosine distance on `vec_papers`

Without it, the backend falls back to:
1. FTS5 full-text search on `papers_fts` (if the virtual table exists)
2. Plain `LIKE` search on `title` and `abstract`

## OpenAlex Enrichment

`/paper/{id}` automatically enriches meta-only papers:
1. Checks `enriched_cache` — served instantly if found
2. Fetches from `https://api.openalex.org/works/{id}`
3. Reconstructs abstract from inverted index
4. Caches result in `enriched_cache` forever (use `force=true` to re-fetch)

Set `OPENALEX_EMAIL` to your email to get into the OpenAlex polite pool
(10 req/s instead of 100k/day limit).






